# Northside Intelligence — Cursor Rules

## UI capitalization

Apply Title Case to all button labels, CTAs, nav actions, and short UI chrome (badges, tabs, pill filters) unless the control is intentionally compact (then ALL CAPS is acceptable).

Examples:
- Get Started
- Sign In / Sign Up / Sign Out
- Create Account
- Open Tool
- Explore Tools
- Verify & Continue

Use normal sentence capitalization only for paragraph-style body copy, descriptions, and long-form content — not for buttons, headings, or bold title text unless explicitly requested otherwise.

Do not use arrow suffixes on button text (e.g. prefer "Open Dashboard" over "Open dashboard →").
